# Project Agent Guidance

## Category Routing (oh-my-openagent)

| Category | Model | Trigger |
|----------|-------|------|
| `quick` | local (gpt-4o-mini → workstation) | <20 lines, single file, typo/config/rename |
| `unspecified-low` | local (gpt-4.1 → workstation) | 20-200 lines, multi-file, bug fix, test writing |
| `unspecified-high` | Claude Sonnet max | Complex implementation, deep context needed |
| `ultrabrain` | Claude Opus max | >200 lines, cross-repo, architecture, migration |
| `deep` | Claude Opus max | Root cause analysis, pattern investigation |
| `visual-engineering` | Gemini 3.1 Pro | React, CSS/Tailwind, animations, design systems |
| `writing` | local (gpt-4.1 → workstation) | CHANGELOG, README, docs, PR descriptions |
| `artistry` | Gemini 3.1 Pro | Creative/unconventional — use when standard fails |
| `draft` | local (gpt-4.1 → workstation) | First-pass implementation |
| `verify` | Claude Sonnet | Review and correct a local draft |
| `speculative` | local → verify | Medium complexity with uncertain confidence |

### Routing Heuristics

Use the cheapest model that can do the job. Escalate only when needed:

- **Lines changed < 20, single file** → `quick`
- **Lines changed 20–200, multi-file** → `unspecified-low`
- **Lines changed >200 or cross-repo impact** → `ultrabrain`
- **UI/visual work** → `visual-engineering` regardless of size
- **Docs/prose only** → `writing`
- **Deep investigation, root cause** → `deep`
- **Uncertain confidence, medium complexity** → `speculative`

Expected distribution: ~60% local, ~30% Claude Sonnet, ~10% Claude Opus.

## Code Standards
- Functions: <50 lines, cyclomatic complexity <10, line width <100 chars
- No comments unless asked
- No speculative features, no premature abstraction
- Replace, don't deprecate
- Security-first: never expose credentials, validate inputs, sanitize outputs
